      <bioghist>
         
         <head>Historical Note</head>
         
         <p>The Edgemont Community Center was incorporated in 1941 in Durham, NC,
        as an autonomous, service oriented center located in a low-income white
        neighborhood beset by numerous social problems. The center came to serve a more
        racially mixed population in later years.</p>
      
      </bioghist>
      
